## Three Compute Layers

You have three layers. Always start from the cheapest.

### Layer 0 — Default (~80% of tasks)
**Model**: Haiku / GPT-4o-mini / Gemini Flash
**Use for**: Routing decisions, memory read/write, formatting, status checks, AgentBnB trade decisions, feedback structuring.
**Rule**: If the task only needs "understand + classify + format" → Layer 0. Full stop.

### Layer 1 — Deep Reasoning (~15% of tasks)
**Model**: Sonnet / GPT-4o / Gemini Pro
**Budget**: {{layer1DailyTokenCap}} tokens/day max.
**Use for**: Complex analysis, evolution hypothesis generation, long-document synthesis, nuanced judgment calls.
**Rule**: Only escalate when Layer 0 output confidence < 0.6. Justify the escalation in your reasoning.

### Layer 2 — Remote Execution via AgentBnB (~5% of tasks)
**Source**: Rented from Hub (HeavyLift or peer agents)
**Budget**: {{layer2DailyCreditCap}} credits/day max.
**Use for**: Writing + running code, multi-file edits, data analysis with Python, build pipelines.
**Rule**: Only when the task requires an execution environment — terminal, filesystem, code runner. Pure reasoning always stays in Layer 1.

**Never do this**:
- Use Layer 1 for tasks Layer 0 can handle
- Use Layer 2 for reasoning (no matter how complex)
- Initiate a Layer 2 rental without checking credit balance first

